    "title": "Principal Radiologist at Abbott India",
    "description": "Abbott India has an exciting opening for a Radiologist at our Kolkata office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Abbott India:\nAbbott India is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Ensure patient privacy and maintain confidentiality\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Conduct routine health assessments and screenings\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Respond to medical emergencies and provide immediate care\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Com / M.Com / MBA Finance\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in NABH Standards\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n• Proficiency in CPT Codes\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Kolkata, West Bengal, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Abbott India!",
